	<Title>
		Hormone replacement therapy: Cause of vaginal bleeding?
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Some forms of hormone replacement therapy may cause vaginal bleeding. Learn more.
	</Abstract>
	<Question>
		I&apos;m taking hormone therapy for menopause symptoms, and my monthly menstrual periods have returned. Is this normal?
	</Question>
